  <prompt>
    Add a `compose_summarize_request` handler to the Conversation
    (Assistant) pane. When received, open a fetch stream against
    `/api/compose/action/compose-summarize` (SSE endpoint from task 097),
    consume events, and progressively render response tokens in the
    pane's chat-like surface.

    Subscribe pattern:
      usePaneEvent('conversation', (event) => {
        if (event.type === 'compose_summarize_request') {
          void handleComposeSummarize(event);
        }
        // ...existing chat handlers unchanged
      });

    Fetch loop (Web Streams API):
      const response = await authenticatedFetch(url, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {'Accept': 'text/event-stream',
                  'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
        body: JSON.stringify(bodyPayload),
      });
      const reader = response.body!.getReader();
      const decoder = new TextDecoder();
      let buffer = '';
      while (true) {
        const { done, value } = await reader.read();
        if (done) break;
        buffer += decoder.decode(value, { stream: true });
        // split on \n\n; process each "data: {...}" event
        // append token to conversation state; call setState/dispatch
      }

    Progress events: display in a subtle "Working…" affordance in the
    pane. Token events: append to the current AI response bubble.
    Terminal `data: [DONE]` closes the bubble. Error events: render as an
    inline error state.

    ComposeWorkspace's existing local Summarize state (summaryStatus,
    summaryText, summaryError, dismissSummary) is REMOVED — the state
    now lives in ConversationPane's chat model.

    Verify:
      1. Click Summarize in Compose toolbar → dispatch event → pane opens
         a new AI turn → tokens stream in progressively → terminal renders
      2. Errors show inline (not as a top-level banner)
      3. Existing chat functionality (playbook selection, etc.) is intact
      4. Test with mock EventSource / fetch stream
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend engineer specializing in SSE stream consumption + React state
